# CODEOWNERS — mirror-side defense in depth.
#
# The PRIMARY CODEOWNERS enforcement for SDK paths lives in the monorepo
# root (Juvera-AI/juvera_ai/.github/CODEOWNERS). That's the file that
# actually gates PRs to the source-of-truth paths whose changes will sync
# downstream into this mirror.
#
# This file is mostly documentation: it surfaces the intended owners of
# SDK paths if someone opens a PR against this mirror directly. Such PRs
# would be wiped by the next sync from the monorepo anyway, so the
# enforcement value here is marginal — but having the file documents
# intent for any human looking at the mirror's source.
#
# Edit @handles in BOTH this file and the monorepo root CODEOWNERS
# whenever maintainership changes.

# Workflows + packaging — anything that affects how the package is built
# or published. PRs to these paths must be approved by a maintainer.
.github/                    @RocketRaccoon @vinayakraja
pyproject.toml              @RocketRaccoon @vinayakraja
MANIFEST.in                 @RocketRaccoon @vinayakraja

# Vendored data (pricing catalog) — silent changes to numbers here would
# mis-report ROI for every user.
juvera_sdk/data/            @RocketRaccoon @vinayakraja
